gomodel:SYNGO_389  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Confocal immunofluorescence staining of the calyx of Held and its axon from a P9 rat brainstem slice using the dye Alexa 488 showing the structure of the calyx terminal and the thick calyx axon. Afterwards the slice was fixed and labeled with antibodies against alpha3-NKA (ATP1A3, red) and vGluT1 (blue, a synaptic vesicle marker). Immunoreactivity for alpha3-NKA (red) was located presynaptically at the calyx of Held.. Experimental description: \"Confocal immunofluorescence staining of the calyx of Held and its axon from a P9 rat brainstem slice...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
